2017 WW11 Purley-FPGA Server SKX H0/LBG B1 Silver Release Announcement (BKC #17)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW11 Purley-FPGA Server SKX H0/LBG B1 Silver release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n RHEL7.3\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

\n

\n
\n
\n \n \n \n \n
\n

Key Workaround (detail guide is here)

\n\n

Please use PCIe Video card\ninstead of onboard BMC video due to known BMC issue

\n\n

 

Pedigree and Board\nJumper Settings: guide

\n\n\n\n

Note: Only mandatory and necessary optional rework\nis implemented by BKC team

Mandatory rework FPGA JTAG chain missing CPU1 TCK resistor

Mandatory rework to replace FPGA KR RX AC Caps

Mandatory rework add a pull down to RSMRST

Mandatory rework to update VR FW

CPLD updates to address IFWI issue with 2 SKX FPGA\nCPUs populated

Required\nCPLD updates to address reset and FSC issues
